<TITLE> Vets told to curb trans-border animal diseases </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 31 (bdnews24.com)  The livestock minister has asked the veterinary specialists to set modern techniques for in generating and preserving livestock resources. Regional cooperation as well as national initiative were important in curbing and controlling animal diseases, Abdul Latif Biswas said Tuesday at the launch of a conference of chief veterinary officers of the SAARC countries at a hotel in Dhaka. "We have to extend regional cooperation in exchanging information on animal diseases, avoiding animal products, close monitoring of the diseases and research programme," he said. He stressed the need for a strong foundation of regional cooperation in livestock resources that might help break out of animal diseases in the region. People will be encouraged to form new farms for increasing animal production. That will help employment generation and increasing production of protein for the rural people, Biswas said. The conference would discuss issues on breaking out of bird flu in the SAARC countries, strategies of exchange of information, life saving methods, installing regional vaccine bank on animal diseases and forming surveillance team. It would also formulate work plan to curb trans border animal diseases and initiatives for effective development of livestock sector of the SAARC countries. A total of 40 delegations of the SAARC countries are attending the meet. 
